The Mail said it “could not have put it better” itself: “Whether the court’s judgment was constitutionally appropriate, only history will decide. One thing is certain: this was not a good day for democracy.”

Its major concern, which it shares with the Express, is that “Remoaners” in parliament could delay Brexit or water it down.

Water it down? Isn’t that an interesting concept? The referendum question asked: “Should the United Kingdom remain a member of the European Union or leave the European Union?”

So, as long as parliament fulfils the people’s vote to leave the EU, in what way can it be watered down?